<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
    HSK: add baseline ArmorRating_Sharp / ArmorRating_Blunt to all RH2
    Rimmu-Nation² clothing defs that lack inline values.

    Why: CE warns "penAmount or armorAmount are zero" every time a hit
    lands on apparel that has StuffEffectMultiplierArmor but no base
    ArmorRating to multiply. Without these baselines, the multiplier
    has nothing to scale and the deflection calc trips the warning.

    Coverage: every RNApparel_* / RHApparel_* ThingDef whose statBases
    does NOT already declare ArmorRating_Sharp. Body armor defs in
    Apparel_Armor.xml and the special-set files all declare inline
    ArmorRating_Sharp (e.g. 1.01 for vests) and are excluded by the
    not() predicate. Only clothing/hats/masks/eye+ear pro/scarves/
    bandanas/jackets/pants/shirts pick up the baseline.

    Values: Sharp 0.05 / Blunt 0.10 reflect cloth/synthetic-fiber gear -
    bullets pass through, modest blunt cushioning. The wearer's chosen
    stuff scales these via StuffEffectMultiplierArmor (existing 0.10-0.20
    on most clothing).

    Loads as ZZ_* so it runs after the existing CE patches that may
    inject statBases - we add to whatever final shape the upstream
    patches produced.
-->
<Patch>
    <Operation Class="PatchOperationAdd">
        <xpath>Defs/ThingDef[(starts-with(defName, "RNApparel_") or starts-with(defName, "RHApparel_")) and not(statBases/ArmorRating_Sharp)]/statBases</xpath>
        <value>
            <ArmorRating_Sharp>0.05</ArmorRating_Sharp>
            <ArmorRating_Blunt>0.10</ArmorRating_Blunt>
        </value>
    </Operation>
</Patch>
